race.description: Steel & Stone Services F&M Maiden Handicap
race.comment: Tricky and the market moves should prove instructive. CRIMSON WINGS (4) didn't have the best of it at Rosehill on debut ($9.50) and was immediately tipped out. Resumes today owning a comfortable Canterbury trial win, suggesting a bold return. Maps for the run of the race and appeals most. DENISE'S GAL (5) had been well educated and just missed at Wyong on debut, riding the speed. She also has a handy barrier and won't have to improve much to be in the finish. WEEKEND MARKET (3) comes out of the same race beaten less than 2L. She was found to have a slow recovery rate, but is back after 17 days, so all must be in order. Has an awkward gate, but the 1.5kg claim assists. HAD IT ALL (6) resumes for a leading metro stable and has had a stack of trials since his solid debut run at Warwick Farm 423 days ago. It's an ask, but he has an inside gate and has shown enough to deserve a close market watch.
